node.text: Baby2Baby is proud to serve as the leader of the Baby2Baby National Network, a group of 43, like-minded organizations who distribute basic essentials to children living in poverty across the country. We recently gathered for our 2020 summit for a conversation on how to better serve children in our communities impacted by COVID-19. Throughout the pandemic, our network has put millions of critical items into the hands of the most vulnerable children in Los Angeles, New York City, Miami, Seattle, Dallas, Denver, Nashville, Atlanta, Chicago, Baltimore, Washington DC, Portland and more.

node.text: From drive-through distributions to deliveries on children's doorsteps to shipments across the country, team Baby2Baby is committed to providing diapers, formula, soap, shampoo, baby food, masks, hand sanitizer and so much more to families who are struggling to make ends meet as a result of COVID-19. When we can provide these items, families can use their extremely limited funds to pay their rent, put food back on the table and keep their children safe.

node.text: Thank you to everyone who joined our Baby2Baby family for an Instagram Live in honor of Mother's Day!  Our Angels crafted, baked and danced their hearts out in support of Baby2Baby's work providing basic essentials to mothers struggling as a result of COVID-19.  A huge shout out to our sponsors @Nordstrom @BuildaBearFoundation @Albertsons @Nuna_USA @OldNavy @AfterpayUSA @InfantinoBaby and @Netflix for stepping up to support the moms we serve across the country in honor of Mother's Day - thanks to their generosity, we can distribute 10 million more diapers and basic essentials 💚💚💚.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Baby2Baby on August 12, 2021. May be an image of fire and outdoors.

node.text:
Baby2Baby has provided tens of thousands of basic essentials including diapers, wipes, soap, shampoo and hand sanitizer to children displaced by the devastating Dixie Fire, the largest single fire ever in California history.  These items will help provide relief to families who were already struggling as a result of the pandemic and now have to face the catastrophic impact of this record-breaking fire. 

📷: AP Photo/Noah Berger

node.text: Through our COVID relief efforts, Baby2Baby has distributed 100 MILLION items to children in 140 cities across the country impacted by the pandemic. Link in bio to help us continue supporting the most vulnerable families with the basic essentials they deserve.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Baby2Baby on August 09, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing, footwear and outdoors.

node.text: These smiles are brought to you from our friends at @happyhannas who donated an incredible $4.6 MILLION worth of clothing to Baby2Baby! This extraordinary gift will help us reach hundreds of thousands of children across the country just in time for back to school. 💚

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Baby2Baby on August 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: Our #Baby2BabyRisingHero is 7-year old Ray Loyd of Anderson, Indiana who has been putting together backpacks filled with essential items for children in need at her local children's hospital. Ray, the thoughtfulness and care you put into “Ray’s Journey Packs” is truly inspiring and we can’t wait to see what you do next!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Baby2Baby on August 04, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person and child.

node.text: With COVID cases rising across the US, the children we serve remain the most vulnerable.  Baby2Baby has already distributed over THREE MILLION masks to keep students protected as they return to in-person learning beginning this month and will continue to provide safety items to the children who need them most.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Baby2Baby on August 02, 2021 tagging @childrensplace. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Jumping for joy from a donation of $1 MILLION worth of clothing, backpacks, shoes and more from @childrensplace for the children we serve across the country as they prepare to get back to the classroom after an unprecedented year.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Baby2Baby on August 02, 2021 tagging @childrensplace. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing and outdoors.
Photo by Baby2Baby on August 02, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, child, outdoors and tree.
Photo by Baby2Baby on August 02, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, child, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Baby2Baby has hundreds of thousands of diapers on the way to families in some of the most impoverished communities across the country that are seeing a rise in COVID cases including Arkansas, Missouri, Alabama, Mississippi, Louisiana and South Carolina.  These essential items will support parents still struggling to afford diapers, food and basic essentials for their babies after 16 months of the pandemic.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Baby2Baby on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, child and standing.

node.text: You can still help fulfill a child's back to school wishlist through our Student2Student program!  Email student2student@baby2baby.org to be matched with a child and provide the supplies they need to get back to the classroom. 💚🎒

node.text: Our #WCW goes out to these lovely (and generous) ladies for helping get the children we serve prepared with all of the essentials they need for the new school year!
